So notice whatever we get up
here that's a positive value,

00:04:20.485 --> 00:04:22.394
we're essentially going
to, if we're dividing it

00:04:22.394 --> 00:04:27.393
by -0.1, that's like
multiplying it by -10,

00:04:27.393 --> 00:04:30.136
so it's going to become
a very negative value,

00:04:30.136 --> 00:04:33.894
and if instead of it
being -3.1, imagine if it

00:04:33.894 --> 00:04:37.352
was -3.01, and this would be a 01 here.

00:04:37.352 --> 00:04:40.570
This would be a 01 here,
and this would be a 01 here.

00:04:40.570 --> 00:04:44.219
And so this denominator,
you're dividing by -0.01,

00:04:44.219 --> 00:04:46.887
it's going to be even
larger negative value,

00:04:46.887 --> 00:04:49.452
so you're going to
approach negative infinity.

00:04:49.452 --> 00:04:50.960
So it's going to be one
of these two choices.

00:04:50.960 --> 00:04:52.358
Now let's think about what happens

00:04:52.358 --> 00:04:54.942
